# Testing Guidelines

## Overview
For specific workflows and patterns:
- TDD Process: See `tdd-workflow.mdc`
- State Management Testing: See `state-management.mdc`
- Error Testing: See `error-handling.mdc`

## Coverage Requirements
- Minimum 80% code coverage required
- 100% coverage for business logic
- All error scenarios must be tested
- Test both success and failure paths
- Include integration tests for API calls

## Test Structure

### Application Layer Tests
#### Cubit Tests
- Test initialization (success and error scenarios)
- Test action execution (loading, success, error states)
- Test concurrent action prevention
- Verify analytics tracking
- Test cleanup on close

### Infrastructure Layer Tests
#### Service Tests
- Test successful operations
- Test error handling
- Test dependency interactions
- Test resource cleanup

### Presentation Layer Tests
#### Widget Tests
- Test loading states
- Test error states
- Test success states
- Test user interactions
- Test localization
- Test screen size adaptations

## Best Practices
- Mock all external dependencies
- Use bloc_test for testing Cubits
- Implement golden tests for critical UI components
- Test edge cases and boundary conditions
- Group related tests using describe/test blocks
- Write meaningful test descriptions
- Follow Arrange-Act-Assert pattern

## Test Data
- Use factory methods for test data
- Create separate test fixtures
- Use meaningful test data
- Avoid hardcoded values
- Document test data assumptions 